22/10/2009
THE HAGUE, Netherlands -- Former Bosnian Serb leader Radovan Karadzic has informed the UN war crimes tribunal that he plans to boycott the start of his trial Monday (October 26th). Karadzic sent a letter to the tribunal reiterating that his defence is "not ready". He is charged with genocide, war crimes and crimes against humanity, stemming from the Bosnian conflict, including the 1995 massacre of 8,000 Muslim men and boys in Srebrenica. (BBC - 22/10/09)
